descript.abstract: Canada Provinces represents the Canadian provinces and territories as well as coastlines, international boundaries, provincial boundaries, and demographics. The boundaries are digitized from CanMap®.
descript.purpose: Canada Provinces provides the provinces and territories of Canada with detail appropriate for national, regional, and local levels.
descript.supplinf: Largest scale when displaying the data: 1:50,000.

procstep.procdesc:
The data set is a fully georeferenced, purely digital product. The boundaries are digitized from CanMap. Source data ranges from municipal mapping at a very large scale of 1:2,000 or larger, to a medium scale of 1:50,000 scale from NTDB*. Source time period of content ranges from a few to several years (as in the case of NTDB*).
*NTDB is the National Topographic Data Base, developed and maintained by Natural Resources Canada.

The following steps were performed by ESRI: Extracted data set from DMTI Spatial™ Canadian Data Bundle. Clipped the features to the coastline and adjusted attributes. Created ArcGIS® layer file (.lyr), projection file (.prj), and spatial indices.

horizpa.horizpar: The positional accuracy ranges from sub-meter (GPS derived) to 5 meters (1:50,000 National Topographic Data Base (NTDB) areas) or greater, in the case of Northern areas in Canada not covered by NTDB, namely, most of Nunavut, much of Northwest Territories and northern parts of British Columbia, Alberta, Manitoba, Ontario and Quebec.

dataqual.logic: No duplicate features are present. The shapefile is converted to SDC (Smart Data Compression) format in ArcSDE®. This verifies and validates the geometry.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
